captions.text: Hello Disney Car Toys.

Here and
today I have a very special treat for you.

We're going to make special Play-Doh
treats based off of this breakfast time
playdate Hello Kitty set.
And to make our Play-Doh treats,

we're going to use this
Minnie Mouse Flipping Fun play kitchen.

We'll need to use the oven,
the refrigerator, the cutting board, and
even the mixer.

Here are all the play food that
comes with Donut Time play set.

Let's put our Hello Kitty cereal on
the shelf, we won't be needing that today.
Because we're going to be making donuts.

Now to make a strawberry
Hello Kitty donut,

we need pink dough, little bit of butter,
and then some Hello Kitty milk.

Alrighty, we have all of
the ingredients in our bowl.
Let's turn on our mixer.

[SOUND] Awe, and
look at that nice pink dough.
This is perfect.

Now to shape our doughnut,
just roll your ball of dough.

And then you want to flatten
it out a little bit, but
you don't wanna make it too flat.

It's really important to start with a ball
first though cause that gives you the nice
smooth edges.

To make the donut hole
is actually pretty easy.
Just take the end of your roller and

then press the roller into
the middle of the donut.
Press pretty hard, and ta-da.

And now we have to roll out
some hot pink Play-Doh for
some delicious strawberry frosting.

You want your frosting to be nice and
thin.
Just lay it over your donut.

Then stick your finger in the middle of
the donut just to break up the frosting.

Next on the sides of the donut
you wanna fold in your frosting.
[MUSIC]

Once all your frosting is folded in
sticking to the donut just take your

Play-Doh knife and
cut off the excess Play-Doh.
[MUSIC]
And now our donut is beautifully frosted.

Now we need to move on
to Hello Kitty's ears.

Just take two balls of Play-Doh and
form it with your fingers into triangles.
[MUSIC]

Then just attach the ear
to the top of your donut.
[MUSIC]
And now for the sprinkles, yay.
That's my favorite part of a donut.

I'm going to use yellow Play-Doh for
the sprinkles.

Just rip tiny little pieces of Play-Doh
off from our Play-Doh ball and
form them into sprinkle shapes.
There you go.
22 sprinkles ought to do it.

And now our donut's almost
complete with the sprinkles.
We just need the hair bow.

For the bow, just roll a little
ball of dark purple Play-Doh.
You flatten it out a little bit.

And then attach the ball of
Play-Doh to two side bow pieces.

Now I'll just place the bow over
Hello Kitty's right donut ear.
Press down just so it stays on well.
And yay, now we have our donut.
This one looks better than the toy one.
Now it's time to get back to baking.
This time I'm going to make a cupcake.

For the cupcake, we'll need some chocolate
dough, butter, three eggs, and milk.
First, I'll add the butter.
Nice big stick.
The eggs.

You know,
I'll just throw the whole shell in there.
[LAUGH] They're just Play-Doh eggs, right?
The last ingredient is our Play-Doh milk.
Okay let's put the bowl in the mixer.

And press the heart button
to get the mixer going.
Wow, look at that cupcake batter.
That's perfect.

Now Play-Doh's a little
different than regular dough.

For this dough, we just need to roll
it out into a nice, smooth ball, and
then just drop it into the cupcake holder.
Now we just have to bake our cupcake.
Let's see here.

We'll bake it at 375, and
we'll try six minutes.
Open up the oven and, you know what?
Let's just toss the cupcake in there.
Ding, it's ready.
Let's see how it turned out.
Oh, it looks pretty good.
Now I just need to frost our cupcake.

For the frosting I'm using
special extra soft Play-Doh plus.
Oh wow it smells so good.
This cupcake looks really tasty.
But you know what?
We're missing something.
We need the cherry on top.

Here's our Play-Doh treats, but you know
we need something to wash this down.

Luckily Hello Kitty has
her own little coffee cup.

Let's sweeten this thing
up a little bit though.
Mm some whipped cream.

Now I can out the lid on, and
stir it with my Hello Kitty bow.

Here are all the delicious Hello Kitty
Play-Doh treats that we made today.

please click like and subscribe.

Click on a picture to watch
